{{<html}}
{{$main}}

{{& page.contents}}

<section class="hero primary">
    <div class="wrapper">
        <picture>
            <source
                srcset="/happyapps/images/logos/happyapps-logo~dark.png"
                media="(prefers-color-scheme: dark)"
                >
            <img
                src="/happyapps/images/logos/happyapps-logo.png"
                alt="Logo of {{site.title}}"
                title="{{site.title}}"
                >
        </picture>
        <h2>A blog on building human centered products, teams, and AI Engineering.</h2>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="book">
  <div class="wrapper">
      <header>
          <h2>Featured Article</h2>
          <p>This current series of 4 articles addresses how to articulate customer and user requirements across cross-functional teams. from product to engineering, quality control while looping in marketing and comm. These series will describe how to leverage the Jobs to Done framework at each step to ensure customer centricity but also how to use Gherkins as foundation for alignment across all expertise in an organisation</p>
      </header>

      <div class="grid grid-422">    
          <div class="info">
            <h3>The waterfall trap</h3>
            <p>Historically, many organisations operated with a waterfall-like model where product managers or business analysts would create detailed specifications that engineers would implement. Engineering teams would receive “clearer guidance upfront” with regular check-ins to ensure alignment. This approach treats engineers primarily as implementers who translate requirements into code.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="centered more-posts">
            <a class="button" href="/blog/posts/page/1">Read Article</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      
    
  </div>
</section>


<section class="">
    <div class="wrapper">
        {{#empty(site.context.posts)}}
        Empty.
        {{/empty(site.context.posts)}}
        {{^empty(site.context.posts)}}
        <div class="grid grid-221">
            {{#site.context.posts}}
            {{> partials.blog.post}}
            {{/site.context.posts}}
        </div>
        {{/empty(site.context.posts)}}

        <div class="centered more-posts">
            <a class="button" href="/happyapps/blog/posts/page/1">Browse all posts</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

